{
  "texts": [
    "In common with other applications of AI in the medical domain, high-stake clinical decisions have ethical and medicolegal consequences that demand defensibility.",
    "Research done to develop explainable AI for transparency of decision-making (Wadden, 2022; Durań and Jongsma, 2021; Minh et al., 2022) and to understand algorithmic discrimination (Obermeyer et al., 2019; Heinrichs, 2022) is underdeveloped in many relevant applications.",
    "It remains important to be cognisant of how AI tools are designed so that their outputs are interpreted in the context of their limitations and strengths (Scott et al., 2021; Couckuyt et al., 2022; Sokhansanj and Rosen, 2022).",
    "Regulatory frameworks will need to contend with these issues before widespread adoption of AI in clinical diagnostics is appropriate.",
    "Even where stakes are potentially lower, the reliability of AI must be demonstrated."
  ]
}